&lt;h2 id=&quot;meta&quot;&gt;Meta&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#meta&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous week: (prev:: &lt;a href=&quot;../051---Weekly/2024-W16&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot; data-slug=&quot;051---Weekly/2024-W16&quot;&gt;2024-W16&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not much happened this week. Finishing up work and some last-minute shopping before vacation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;interesting-stuff&quot;&gt;Interesting stuff&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#interesting-stuff&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;favourite-website&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;../110---On-various-subjects/001---On-superlatives&quot; class=&quot;internal alias&quot; data-slug=&quot;110---On-various-subjects/001---On-superlatives&quot;&gt;Favourite&lt;/a&gt; website&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#favourite-website&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../011---Public-Assets/equinox.png&quot; width=&quot;auto&quot; height=&quot;auto&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://equinox.space/&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Equinox&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; — Equinox is a space adventure where the story unfolds as you explore and interact with the environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This self-initiated project illustrates how our studio can help clients tell their own stories through immersive, interactive experiences, making every engagement memorable and deeply captivating for their audience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A lot of projects by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.littleworkshop.fr/&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;LittleWorkshop&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; are amazing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;log&quot;&gt;Log&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#log&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I started to use &lt;a href=&quot;https://omnivore.app/&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Omnivore&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;em&gt;read-it-later&lt;/em&gt; app. In the past I had a few attempts with &lt;a href=&quot;https://getpocket.com/&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Pocket&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but they weren’t wildly successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Omnivore is free and it has an integration with Obsidian: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/omnivore-app/obsidian-omnivore&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;obsidian-omnivore&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From &lt;a href=&quot;../050---Daily/2024-04-22&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot; data-slug=&quot;050---Daily/2024-04-22&quot;&gt;2024-04-22&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

051---Weekly/2024-W18.richContent:
&lt;h2 id=&quot;meta&quot;&gt;Meta&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#meta&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous week: (prev:: &lt;a href=&quot;../051---Weekly/2024-W17&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot; data-slug=&quot;051---Weekly/2024-W17&quot;&gt;2024-W17&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Packing and sightseeing. 🇮🇹&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I didn’t have time (and desire) to read articles and write notes this week, so there’s not much in here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;log&quot;&gt;Log&lt;a role=&quot;anchor&quot; aria-hidden tabindex=&quot;-1&quot; data-no-popover href=&quot;#log&quot; class=&quot;internal&quot;&gt;&lt;svg width=&quot;18&quot; height=&quot;18&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 24 24&quot; fill=&quot;none&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; stroke-width=&quot;2&quot; stroke-linecap=&quot;round&quot; stroke-linejoin=&quot;round&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../011---Public-Assets/myth_of_second_chance.png&quot; width=&quot;auto&quot; height=&quot;auto&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An interesting article on having second chances: &lt;a href=&quot;https://ft.pressreader.com/article/282557318242321&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;The myth of the second chance&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Then, by a complete chance I found this LessWrong article: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/HsxT2cpPWYzTg9tpY/d-and-d-sci&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;D&amp;#x26;D.Sci&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The goal is to adjust your D&amp;#x26;D stats to maximize your chances of success in the Great Quest. I suggest you give it a shoot; if you’d like to see my solution checkout &lt;a href=&quot;../175---LessWrong/Articles/011---D-and-D.Sci&quot; class=&quot;internal alias&quot; data-slug=&quot;175---LessWrong/Articles/011---D-and-D.Sci&quot;&gt;D&amp;#x26;D.Sci&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;../011---Public-Assets/bishop_of_rome.png&quot; width=&quot;auto&quot; height=&quot;auto&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VESCOVO DI ROMA&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;Italian:&lt;/em&gt; bishop of Rome) — is the first title of the Pope given in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annuario_Pontificio&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Annuario Pontificio&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the annual directory of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holy_See&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Holy See&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catholic_Church&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Catholic Church&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://pylint.readthedocs.io/en/latest/user_guide/messages/refactor/use-dict-literal.html&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Pylint 3.2.0-dev0&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; docs link to my article &lt;a href=&quot;https://madebyme.today/blog/python-dict-vs-curly-brackets/&quot; class=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Performance Analysis of Python’s &lt;code&gt;dict()&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;{}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;svg class=&quot;external-icon&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 512 512&quot;&gt;&lt;path d=&quot;M320 0H288V64h32 82.7L201.4 265.4 178.7 288 224 333.3l22.6-22.6L448 109.3V192v32h64V192 32 0H480 320zM32 32H0V64 480v32H32 456h32V480 352 320H424v32 96H64V96h96 32V32H160 32z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. This is really existing.&lt;/p&gt;

