Meta
Source: htmlhead.dev/. The website is hosted onGitHub Pages: github.com/joshbuchea/HEAD.
Recommended Minimum
&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1&quot; /&gt;
&lt;!--
  The above 2 meta tags *must* come first in the &lt;head&gt;
  to consistently ensure proper document rendering.
  Any other head element should come *after* these tags.
 --&gt;
&lt;title&gt;Page Title&lt;/title&gt;

Elements
Valid &lt;head&gt; elements include meta, link, title, style, script, noscript, and base.
Kamil’s favourite
Meta
&lt;!-- Name of web application (only should be used if the website is used as an app) --&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;application-name&quot; content=&quot;Application Name&quot;&gt;

&lt;!-- Theme Color for Chrome, Firefox OS and Opera --&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;theme-color&quot; content=&quot;#4285f4&quot;&gt;

&lt;!-- Short description of the document (limit to 150 characters) --&gt;
&lt;!-- This content *may* be used as a part of search engine results. --&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;description&quot; content=&quot;A description of the page&quot;&gt;
Link
&lt;!-- Helps prevent duplicate content issues --&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;canonical&quot; href=&quot;example.com/article/

&lt;!-- Feeds --&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;alternate&quot; href=&quot;feeds.feedburner.com/example&quot; type=&quot;application/rss+xml&quot; title=&quot;RSS&quot;&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;alternate&quot; href=&quot;example.com/feed.atom&quot; type=&quot;application/atom+xml&quot; title=&quot;Atom 0.3&quot;&gt;
Browsers/Platforms
Google Chrome
&lt;!-- Disable translation prompt --&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;google&quot; content=&quot;notranslate&quot;&gt;

